# Regenerable runtime artifacts — recreated by the running system, never
# meant to be committed. Keeps the repo from re-bloating with ledgers,
# logs, receipts, framebuffers, and per-session state on every run.

# --- Software framebuffers / large binary render output ---
*.rgba32

# --- Append-only audit logs / ledgers / receipts (auto-trimmed at runtime) ---
**/ledger.txt
**/master_ledger.txt
**/master_ledger/master_ledger.txt
*.log
parser.out
**/pieces/debug/frames/session_frame_history.txt
**/pieces/debug/frames/session_receipt_history.txt
**/session/history_archive.txt
**/renderer_pulse.txt
**/rgb_frame_changed.txt
**/frame_changed.txt

# --- Rolling receipt snapshots (bounded by pieces/config/receipts.conf) ---
# Kept small at runtime, but still session-scoped noise for version control.
**/pieces/debug/frames/

# --- Per-session state that is regenerated on launch ---
**/session/.manager.lock
**/session/history.cursor

# --- Build artifacts ---
*.o
